cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with machine learning algorithms that learn personalized models while preserving privacy. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely category as well. The algorithm is fully decentralized, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the trade-off between utility and privacy, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with privacy concerns in the context of personal devices, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) as well.
